❯ what do I use for an admin key and app key?                                                                                                                                           

● Both are just random secret strings you generate yourself — no external service needed.

  Generate them right now on the DGX:
  # App key (goes in APK)
  python3 -c "import secrets; print('APP:',  secrets.token_hex(24))"

  # Admin key (stays on DGX only, never in APK)
  python3 -c "import secrets; print('ADMIN:', secrets.token_hex(24))"

  Example output:
  APP:  a3f9c12e84b7d6f0219e5c3a7f8b4d2e1c0a9f8e
  ADMIN: 9b2e7f4c1a6d3e8f5c2b9a7d4e1f6c3b8a5d2e

  Where each one lives:
  
  ┌──────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │       Key        │                             Where it goes                             │                    Who uses it                     │
  ├──────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ BTC160_APP_KEY   │ Android APK (hardcoded string resource or build config) + DGX env var │ Every phone on every request                       │
  ├──────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ BTC160_ADMIN_KEY │ DGX env var only — never in APK, never on phones                      │ You manually, via curl from the DGX or your laptop │
  └──────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Start the server with both:
  BTC160_APP_KEY=a3f9c12e84b7d6f0... \
  BTC160_ADMIN_KEY=9b2e7f4c1a6d3e8f... \
  bash api_start.sh

  Put the app key in the Android build — add it to local.properties (which is git-ignored) and read it as a BuildConfig field, so it never ends up hardcoded in source control. That's
  the cleanest approach.
  
  The app key leaking is a nuisance (someone could spam your API) but not a financial risk. The admin key leaking would let someone stop your DGX search — keep that one private.
  
